AGI - Two high-level U.S. and Russian delegations met in Saudi Arabia for the most extensive negotiations between the two countries in three years, agreeing to start a planning process of the end of the war in Ukraine and pursue closer cooperation, against the background of the fears of Kiev and of all Europe that Donald Trump can push for an agreement in favor of Vladimir Putin. The Ukrainian President, Volodymyr Zelensky, > not invited to the Riad table and who was in Ankara for talks with Turkish President Recep Tayip Erdogan>, condemned the negotiations "on Ukraine without Ukraine" and asked for "equity" talks that include besides Kiev, the EU, the United Kingdom and Turkey. Erdogan, for his part, described his country as "an ideal guest for possible negotiations between Russia, Ukraine and the United States". After talks at the Diriyah Palace in Riad, which lasted almost five hours, the US Secretary of State, Marco Rubio>, said that the parties agreed to create a high-level team for peace talks in Ukraine and to explore "economic and investment opportunities that will emerge from a positive conclusion of the conflict in Ukraine".
The statements highlighted a radical change in Washington's approach to Moscow, drastically moving away from the efforts of the Biden administration to isolate it. Despite the diplomatic acceleration, little is known of the <a href="https://www.agi.it/estero/news/2025-02-16/conflict-russia-ucraina-trump- meeting-putin-30056833/"> Trump's peace plan</a>&nbsp; for Ukraine or Russia's will to engage, and the Riad meeting offered few new clues. Rubio said "convinced" that Moscow wants to commit itself to a "restricted process" to end the war and has nevertheless assured that an agreement on Ukraine must be "acceptable" for all. "It must be a definitive end of the war, not temporary, as we have seen in the past. We know, it is only the reality of things, that there will be a discussion on the territories and there will be a discussion on security guarantees," he said. The head of the American diplomacy has assured that Europeans - including them excluded from today's talks, but without which a unilateral revocation of economic sanctions against Russia by Washington is hardly possible - will have to "seat at the table at a certain point".
<div </div
Russia at Riyadh gets what he was asking for for years: to deal with the United States, held by the Kremlin the only ones responsible for the war and therefore also the only actor able to stop it. Russian official media praise the Trump administration and its "tentative to settle the pastries committed by Biden and members". The head of the Russian delegation, Foreign Minister Serghei Lavrov, said that he had perceived "a keen interest in removing artificial obstacles to the development of mutually beneficial economic cooperation between Russia and the United States. The implicit reference is to economic sanctions. Lavrov has also been sure that the U.S. has begun to "better understand" Moscow's position, reaffirming on this occasion the categorical opposition of Russia to any contingent of NATO countries on Ukrainian soil and that Russians and Americans not only had "hearded" each other, but were also "understood". Meanwhile, USA and Russia have vowed to bring back their diplomatic representations to pre-crisis levels and decided to "name high-level teams to start working on a solution to the conflict in Ukraine as soon as possible".
&nbsp;
<div </div
Keith Kellogg, the US Special Envoy, is the first officially invested in the task of leading the American negotiation. Another team apart, instead, will be appointed to carry out talks on the most purely bilateral issues. Before the beginning of the talks, Russia had stressed that the resolution of the war in Ukraine was inseparable from the reorganization of European security architecture. Russia has long called for the withdrawal of NATO forces from Eastern Europe, considering the Alliance an existential threat. In particular, he had used this argument to justify his invasion of Ukraine in 2022.
President Donald Trump's administration has been very critical to European allies and unwilling to support Kiev. Zelensky reacted hard to the Riad negotiations, of which he had not even been informed: not only did he postpone his visit to Saudi Arabia scheduled for tomorrow, but also warned that he will never respect the "lasttum" of Moscow. Riad's meeting ended without a date for the expected Putin-Trump summit that US President had speculated could already hold next week, always in the Saudi capital. Russian presidential adviser Yuri Ushakov, also at the negotiating table, noted that it is too early to talk about a rapprochement with the US; However, the official agency Ria Novosti notes, "as our Chinese friends say, a thousand-mile journey begins with a single step>".&nbsp;
<h2>Trump: "More confident for an agreement with Moscow"</h2>
The President of the United States, Donald Trump, said he was more "trustful" in the possibility of an agreement with Moscow after <a href="https://www.agi.it/estero/news/2025-02-18/russia-usa-delegations-riad-destino-Ucraine-30086481/"> the discussions between Americans and Russians at Riad</a> and declared a favorable troops "totally presence in Ukraine" The American President also said he was " disappointed" by Kiev's comments on the absence of Ukraine to Russian-American discussions at Riad. "I think I have the power to end the war," added Donald Trump in front of journalists in Florida.&nbsp;
Washington's leader defined today's talks with Russian officials as "very good", adding that they want to "do something". "They want to stop wild barbarism," he said. "By Russia both Ukraine are losing thousands and thousands of soldiers, and many people have also been killed."
<h3> The sending of troops
The United States will never enlist soldiers in Ukraine even if the President stressed that he did not want to oppose the deployment of troops of a European mission of peace in Ukrainian territory, a possibility of encoding; of which European leaders spoke in a meeting in Paris. "If you want to do it, good. I'm absolutely in favour. If you want to do this, I think it would be right."&nbsp; The United States, he suggested, will not participate "because we are very far away". Trump continued by saying that "no one asked me to remove all American troops from Europe if there was a peace agreement," so I don't think we should do it." He continued: "I don't want to do that. But this question has never been raised."
I will probably meet Putin by February.
Then the announcement of Tycoon himself that anticipates as "probably" will meet his Russian counterpart Vladimir Putin before the end of the month, while trying to reach an agreement to end the war. Trump responded "probably" to a question on the subject while he was leaving a press conference at his Mar-a-Lago estate in Florida.&nbsp;
The President of the United States declared himself "deleted" by Kiev's comments on the absence of Ukraine in the Russian-American confrontation. On Ukraine he added: "I think I have the power to end this war, and I think it's going well. But today I heard: Oh, well, we weren't invited. Well, you've been there for three years. You should have finished it after three years. You should never have started it. You could have made a deal," he said. Ukraine never began the war, which began in February 2022 when Russian President Vladimir Putin invaded the country. Trump said he could reach an agreement for Ukraine "that would give them almost all territory... and no person would be killed > "But," he concluded, "they chose not to do so that way." Trump, speaking from his resort in Mar-a-Lago, Florida, added that Zelensky likes "personally", claiming, without proof, that the leader has a consensus percentage of "four percent". &nbsp;

